race.comment: Keen on CELERITY (15) off the high gate. Former Cummings mare who has had two runs for the new yard and has been close to the winner at each. At top now and looks suited this level. Will stalk out wide and hit the line hard. HARRY GOT STYLES (2) has been good in two recent fourths, the latest beaten less than a length. Has the claim and will be winding up late. COMMANDS SUCCESS (11) resumed with a close second in easier grade but has upside and will be doing best work late.  SALSA FELLOW (7) had just one start last campaign which was in a big field here in the spring but was safely held and went back out to the paddock. Must have had an issue. Won a far richer race than this here over the winter and has won fresh. Definite win chance on best figures.
